        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:32PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 332 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Courtland, or 14 miles north of Moulton, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40-50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Courtland, North Courtland, Hillsboro, Coxey, Cairo, Wheeler, and
Ripley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
